sched: fix regression in scheduler load balance

After commit e4f5g6h ("sched: optimize load balance for NUMA"), we
observed a regression in scheduler throughput on systems with
asymmetric CPU capacities.

The issue is that the NUMA optimization incorrectly assumes all
NUMA nodes have similar CPU capacities. On systems with big.LITTLE
or similar architectures, this leads to tasks being migrated to
slower CPUs unnecessarily.

Fix by checking CPU capacity before applying the NUMA fast path.

